items.content_html:
FF93 supports SHA256 for digest authentication. Docs work can be tracked in #8682

This is draft because I'm still working out the scope of the change. First changes are just improvements to the wording and updating to current specs etc.

Note, most of these are to HTTP Digest stuff. I have since found out that the change is only supported in authentication, not digest (https://bugzilla.mozilla.org/show_bug.cgi?id=472823#c49). But these changes are IMO still useful.

@teoli2003 Just an FYI, I'd appreciate your help to review this when it is done. I think some work needs to be done to expand on the Authorization headers for more than just "basic".

Further, I think perhaps we're missing quite a few fields from Authorization header - or perhaps something else is going on. But as you can see, a lot more than we document are shown here: https://datatracker.ietf.org/doc/html/rfc7616#section-3.4
items.title: FF93 First changes for digest SHA256 support

items.content_html: The page states that the largest of two touching negative margins is used when the reverse is true. The value that is used is the one furthest from zero (i.e. the smallest) based on testing. Alternatively, one could say that the value with the largest absolute value is used.
items.title: Correct negative margin inaccuracy

InterfaceData.json can be generated from this data; before making my initial script robust enough for automatic updates to this repo, I'm submitting the data that can be extracted from there to see if this is indeed an improvement over the currently manually maintained file.
